reviews.text: Fast service. I  Got 20 percent off my order today by signing up my Email address. I ordered a large pizza and a hot a steak and cheese sub. All for $25.00. Not to shabby.

I was lured in with a free cheese pizza. I ordered other items and arrived early for my order. There was only one other person there. Over 15 people were served as my food sat on the oven during my 30 minute wait. Not once did anyone come out to wipe a table or straighten the eating area. When I finally approached them and reminded them about my order I discovered I‚Äôd been staring at it sitting on the oven as I paced back and forth for half an hour. With no apology for the delay they handed me the food that had sat there almost my entire 30 minute wait. I actually paid and went to my car. I almost cried. The fried mushrooms were hard and literally cold. I tried one- burst of cold slimy mushroom juice in breading. I went back in and returned them. The pizza was cold greasy and limp. The Italian sub was fatty thinly sliced meat with little flavor. The meal was beyond bad. The wait unreasonable and there was zero customer service. Repugnant experience.

Country is my favorite pizza! I moved to Winchendon a year ago and I don't get it often anymore, but their Alfredo pizza is my absolute favorite. Their steak tips are superior and their fries are amazing. Definitely recommend it here!

First time visiting, was greeted by a happy employee, and a clean atmosphere. They seem to crank food out, I was served my to-go order in a great time frame. I will definitely be back. Big fan of their cheese and dough.

I order from Country pizza every Friday night. We just ordered two large steak bomb grinders This evening. My steak grinder had barely any steak in them.  I found 3 Pieces of mushrooms and 3 itty bitty onions And no cheese. These grinders are so inconsistent. I‚Äôve ordered them in the past and they‚Äôre either very full of steak with tons of Grizzle with so much grease that is unbearable to eat. Since it so close to home, I patronizes this place every Friday night.  They are extremely busy and charging almost $13 for a large cheese grinder to find this is what they offer when you receive it. I‚Äôm sorry to say that I‚Äôve given them endless count of money to only Receive less than standard food. I really always kept on hoping that they get their act together and be consistent. Sorry to say I‚Äôll have to say goodbye. I wish them the best, but I will never order food from them ever again.
